40Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Reopening: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/40065\r\nThe issue was closed because there is an \"easy fix\", however said easy fix does not work on Windows.\r\n\r\n# Issue\r\nIt is impossible to run `cargo test --doc` on Windows in some environments (particularly corporate environments with tight security). Doctests are created in the default tmp folder for the active user, however said tmp folder may be noexec. \r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10907577/200196916-526eb5a0-bd29-47de-9d26-085e3d948012.png)\r\nTherefore, I would like for the possibility to set the TEMPDIR location on Windows to be specifiable via cargo config (or any other mean).", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/104072/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/104072/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}